<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-06-0947 </DOCNO><TEXT>The discussion on rational energy utilization and renewable raw materialspoints to the generation of biogas as a possible method for fossil fuelssubstitution. The food processing industry is characterized by the useof substrates with high organic contents; hence, biogas technology maywell contribute up to 50% of the primary energy demand of a factory andalso to a meaningful waste disposal. The methods and possible applicationsof biogas technology are exemplified by biogas production from the wastewater of a potato starch factory and from brewery by-products (solids).</TEXT></DOC>